    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-19T19:17:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-19T19:17:00-05:00" n="214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793B.00/7–2251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-19T19:17:00-05:00"
                            >October 19, 1951—7:17 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>849. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>s 269 Jul 19 and 302 Jul 21
                    reported assurances from Dutt that <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> had taken
                    steps convey to <gloss target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> willingness grant asylum. Appears however
                    that either <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> never took such step or <pb
                        facs="0378" n="1836" xml:id="pg_1836"/> message never reached <gloss
                        target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss>. Dept notes Tibetan informants believe <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> has obstructed and discouraged <gloss
                        target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss> plans.</p>
                <p>Dept believes next few weeks critical period for Tibetan consideration
                    Sino-Tibetan agreement and possible flight <gloss target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss>. It
                    therefore appropriate make further urgent effort persuade <gloss target="#t_DL1"
                        >DL</gloss> leave Tibet and repudiate agreement. [Name deleted] . . . .
                    Request soonest views Emb and ConGen re following proposal.</p>
                <p>Suggest Emb confidentially inform Bajpai or Dutt (whichever you believe more
                    likely be responsive) that Emb concerned by reports Tibetans feel strongly
                    impending loss Tibetan autonomy. Many influential Tibetans reportedly believe
                        <gloss target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss>’s present plight due lack of sympathy and
                    support from <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>. Inquire whether <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> has similar reports and request <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> appraisal Tibet developments. Emb may comment
                    it wld be most unfortunate if simple misunderstanding by Tibetans has
                    deleterious effect on Tibet and possibly on personal safety <gloss
                        target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss>. Suggest point out misunderstanding might have
                    arisen from fact Dayal had not received instrs when Shakabpa made tentative
                    inquiry Jul. Emb reports suggest assurances expressed by Dutt to Emb apparently
                    did not reach <gloss target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss>. Might be appropriate at this
                    point to inquire whether <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> has info indicating
                        <gloss target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss> did receive <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> assurances.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> Record shows US cannot rely on initiative
                        <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> in new approach to <gloss
                        target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss>. However, Dept hopes new Emb approach to <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> may result in <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> statements providing basis for Emb message to <gloss
                        target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss> indicating receipt by Emb of recent assurance
                    from <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> that asylum or transit privilege will
                    be granted <gloss target="#t_DL1">DL</gloss> on request.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
